        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-[#10B981] pl-6 py-5 bg-emerald-50 rounded-r mb-6">
          <p class="text-sm font-black text-emerald-600 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE BEFORE</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Marcus Chen, luxury agent in San Francisco. $2.5M+ average sale price. Working 18 months. Had 3 luxury listings in past year. Website: basic Squarespace template from 2020. Looked "professional enough" he thought. Luxury sellers interviewing agents: visited his site, clicked "back" within 10 seconds. Site didn't scream "luxury specialist." Looked like every other realtor site. Lost $1M+ listings to competitors with better digital presence. Stuck at 3 luxury closings/year. Frustrated.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-[#10B981] pl-6 py-5 bg-emerald-50 rounded-r mb-6">
          <p class="text-sm font-black text-emerald-600 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE FIX</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Invested in Framer custom site with video walkthroughs for every listing. Property galleries with professional photography. Matterport 3D virtual tours embedded. Neighborhood guides with local insights. "Sold" gallery with luxury closings. Premium typography and whitespace. Modern, luxury feel throughout. Build time: 2 weeks. Cost: $0 (Framer free tier during build), then $15/month. Site felt like $5M+ listings, not $500K.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-[#10B981] pl-6 py-5 bg-emerald-50 rounded-r mb-6">
          <p class="text-sm font-black text-emerald-600 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE AFTER</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">12 months later: Marcus closed 6 luxury listings vs. 3 previous year. 2x more luxury closings. Average sale price: $2.8M vs. $2.5M before. Total luxury volume: $16.8M vs. $7.5M previous year. At 3% commission: $504K vs. $225K. That's $279K more in commission from website upgrade alone. Luxury sellers now calling him exclusively. Site justifies his premium commission. Built referral base from impressed sellers.</p>
