          <p class="text-sm font-black text-emerald-600 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE 90-DAY BREAKDOWN</p>
          <ul class="text-gray-700 space-y-2 text-sm">
            <li><strong>Month 1:</strong> Framer site launched with premium design and video walkthroughs. 2 luxury seller inquiries vs. 0-1/month average. Both listed. Sold 1 for $2.7M ($81K commission). Revenue: $81K from one luxury closing vs. $0-50K/month average before. Site paid for itself 5x over in month 1 alone</li>
            <li><strong>Month 2:</strong> Added Matterport virtual tours. Time on site: 47 seconds ‚Üí 2:34. Showing requests: 67% increase. Qualified buyers only (tire-kickers filtered out by 3D tour). Closed 2 luxury listings: $5.6M total ($168K commission). Referral from impressed seller: another luxury listing lead</li>
            <li><strong>Month 3:</strong> Added neighborhood guides and market insights blog. Seller leads from content: 8 inquiries vs. 1/month before. Closed 3 luxury listings: $8.4M ($252K commission). 3-month total: 6 luxury closings, $16.8M volume, $504K commission. Previous 12-month total: 3 closings, $7.5M volume, $225K commission. Website upgrade: +$279K in 90 days</li>
            <li><strong>Lesson:</strong> Luxury sellers expect premium presentation. Your website signals your market position. Template site = "average realtor." Custom site = "luxury specialist." For luxury agents, design isn't aesthetic‚Äîit's positioning.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-6 pt-6 border-t-2 border-emerald-200">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <strong>The brutal truth:</strong> Your website is your first showing. Luxury sellers interview multiple agents before listing. Your site is often their first impression. If it looks average, they assume your service is average. If it looks premium, they assume you deliver premium results. One extra $1.5M luxury closing at 3% = $45K commission. Custom site pays for itself 3x over with ONE extra closing.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-2">
            I rated Squarespace 9.3/10 for most agents because stunning property galleries and MLS iframe integration sell homes. But if you're targeting luxury listings? Framer or Webflow custom design justifies your premium commission.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- THE HARD TRUTH -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-gradient-to-br from-red-50 to-orange-50">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-4xl">
      <div class="border-[3px] border-red-400 p-6 md:p-8">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-6">The Hard Truth About Agent Websites</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-red-600 uppercase tracking-wider font-black mb-8">Mistakes that cost agents millions in lost commissions</p>

