              <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Luxury agent with Framer custom site: 6 luxury listings in 12 months. Same-market agent with Squarespace template: 3 luxury listings. 2x difference. Why? Luxury sellers expect premium presentation. Template site says "I work with everyone." Custom site says "I specialize in luxury." One extra $1.5M closing at 3% = $45K commission. Custom site pays for itself 3x over with ONE extra closing. Template sites work for residential. Custom required for luxury.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 bg-red-500 text-white flex items-center justify-center font-black text-xl">2</div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">No IDX/MLS native integration means manual updates</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Important reality: NO DIY builder has native IDX/MLS. All require third-party iframe embeds (IDX Broker, MLS/IDX, Showcase IDX). These cost $50-200/month separately. If budget doesn't allow IDX: manually showcase 5-10 featured listings. Update when sold or pending. Not ideal but workable starting out. Don't choose builder expecting native MLS syncing‚Äîit doesn't exist. Budget for IDX separately if live listings matter.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 bg-red-500 text-white flex items-center justify-center font-black text-xl">3</div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Slow mobile galleries lose 73% of buyer showing requests</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Buyer driving neighborhood: sees "for sale" sign. Searches agent site on phone. Slow-loading gallery: they leave. Fast mobile-optimized gallery: they schedule showing. 73% of real estate searches are mobile. If your property gallery doesn't work on phone, you're losing 3 out of 4 showing requests. Wix struggles with image-heavy mobile loads. Framer and Squarespace deliver fast mobile galleries. Mobile optimization isn't optional‚Äîit's survival.</p>
