            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">No market insights blog = 5x fewer seller leads</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Realtor without blog: 58 seller leads in 12 months. Realtor publishing weekly market insights: 312 seller leads in 12 months. 5x difference. Why? Sellers search "what's my home worth" before interviewing agents. They find your content, trust your expertise, list with you. Blog = authority = SEO = free listings. No blog = relying on referrals and Zillow leads (expensive). Weekly market updates = seller lead pipeline.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 bg-red-500 text-white flex items-center justify-center font-black text-xl">5</div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Virtual tours filter serious buyers, save wasted showings</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Agent added Matterport 3D virtual tours: time on site 47 seconds ‚Üí 2:34 (3x more). Showing requests: 67% increase. But conversion: 47% higher. Why? Virtual tours filter serious buyers. Tire-kickers don't spend time in 3D tours. Qualified buyers do. Save 2-3 hours per wasted showing. At 20 showings/month, that's 40-60 hours saved. Time saved = more closings. Virtual tours = better qualified leads = more closings per showing.</p>
